# .NET Full-Stack Project — Cursor Rules

## Tech Stack
- Backend: .NET 10 / C# 13 / ASP.NET Core
- Frontend: Blazor Server (or React/TypeScript — adjust as needed)
- Database: Entity Framework Core with MSSQL
- Testing: xUnit + Moq (backend), bUnit (Blazor) or React Testing Library
- Logging: Serilog (structured JSON)
- Validation: FluentValidation (backend), DataAnnotations (Blazor forms)

## Architecture
- Backend: Clean Architecture (API → Application → Domain → Infrastructure)
- Frontend: Component-based with service injection
- API: RESTful with OpenAI-compatible versioning (/api/v1/...)
- Communication: Frontend calls API via HttpClient / typed HTTP clients
- State: Server-side session or client-side state management (specify which)

## Backend Standards
- File-scoped namespaces
- Nullable reference types enabled
- Async/await everywhere
- CancellationToken on all async methods
- Result<T> pattern for business logic errors
- ProblemDetails for HTTP error responses
- Parameterized queries only

## Frontend Standards (Blazor)
- Components in Pages/ (routable) and Shared/ (reusable)
- Use @inject for service dependencies
- Implement IDisposable on components that subscribe to events
- Loading states: show spinner during async operations
- Error states: display user-friendly messages, never stack traces
- Accessibility: aria labels, keyboard navigation, semantic HTML

## Frontend Standards (React — if applicable)
- TypeScript strict mode (no `any`)
- Functional components with hooks
- Custom hooks for API calls and shared logic
- Error boundaries for graceful failure handling
- Responsive design (mobile-first)

## Security & Compliance (HIPAA)
- NEVER log PHI (patient names, DOBs, SSNs, prescription details)
- NEVER display full SSN on screen (mask as ***-**-1234)
- NEVER store PHI in browser localStorage or sessionStorage
- All API calls require authentication tokens
- Frontend must clear sensitive data from memory on component disposal/navigation
- Forms collecting PHI should indicate "Protected Health Information" visually
- Audit log all data mutations on the backend

## Testing
- Backend: unit tests for services, integration tests for API endpoints
- Frontend: component render tests, interaction tests
- Test naming: MethodName_Scenario_ExpectedResult
- No real PHI in test data

## Cross-Layer Concerns
- When modifying an API endpoint, update the corresponding frontend component
- When adding a new entity, create: migration, repository, service, controller, DTOs, and frontend page
- Validation rules must match between frontend and backend
- Error messages from the API must be displayable in the frontend
